@BrazilianHybrid: The format(well, actually the container) is mkv.
As far as it running on a PS3 is concerned, if you are planning to run it from a pen-drive, no(since a file-size greater than 4GB is not allowed in FAT32).
I suggest you download a 1080p rip of less than 4GB of mp4 format(never download avi, quality sucks) since that should work perfectly, though of very slightly lower quality than an 7GB rip.
